
Binary packet protocol:

[LENGTH][TYPE][TYPE_PAYLOAD]

LENGTH        uint16_t
TYPE          uint8_t
TYPE_PAYLOAD  uint8_t[]

where:
  LENGTH       - length of whole packet. It is encoded in network byte order
  TYPE         - type of packet.
  TYPE_PAYLOAD - packet specific payload.



Current TYPEs:
  TYPE           CODE

  NACK            0x01

  GET_DHT22       0x60
  REPLY_DHT22     0x61


NACK binary packet protocol:

[LENGTH][NACK]

LENGTH        uint16_t
TYPE          uint8_t

where:
  LENGTH      = Length of whole packet. It is encoded in network byte order.
                Must be set to 0x02.

  NACK        = 0x01

NACK packet means that the last packet was rejected.
It may be sent due to invalid packet.



GET_DHT22 binary packet protocol:

[LENGTH][GET_DHT22]

LENGTH        uint16_t
TYPE          uint8_t

where:
  LENGTH      = Length of whole packet. It is encoded in network byte order.
                Must be set to 0x02.

  GET_DHT22   = 0x60



REPLY_DHT22 binary packet protocol:

[LENGTH][REPLY_DHT22][SUCCESS][TEMPERATURE][HUMIDITY]

LENGTH        uint16_t
TYPE          uint8_t
SUCCESS       bool
TEMPERATURE   int32_t
HUMIDITY      int32_t

where:
  LENGTH      = Length of whole packet. It is encoded in network byte order.
                Must be set to 0x04 or 0x0B
                0x04 = sizeof(LENGTH) + sizeof(TYPE) + sizeof(SUCCESS);
                0x0B = 0x04 + sizeof(TEMPERATURE) + sizeof(HUMIDITY);

  REPLY_DHT22 = 0x61

  SUCCESS     = boolean, 0 means that firmware got some error in DHT22 transaction,
                and there is no valid data to return.
                If SUCCESS == 0, there is no TEMPERATURE or HUMIDITY field.

  TEMPERATURE = int32_t, encoded in network byte order.
                This field is (measured temperature * 100).
                  For example:
                    -7.94 is encoded as -794
                    19.38 is encoded as 1938
                Measured temperature in Celcius.

  HUMIDITY    = int32_t, encoded in network byte order.
                This field is (measured humidity * 100).
                  For example:
                  5.59 is encoded as 559.
                Measured relative humidity.
